{'id': 1415255818352, 'title': 'Standard PLA - Daffodil Yellow', 'handle': 'ingeo-pla-daffodil-yellow', 'description': '

Ahhh, the fresh, calming yellow of a patch of daffodils in the spring! Our Daffodil Yellow Standard PLA 3D printer filament will help your 3D prints look fantastically yellow.

Our Standard PLA, or Polylactic Acid, is among the most popular 3D printing materials in the world because it is easy to print and strong. Standard PLA is a hard plastic that produces a barely noticeable, but quite pleasant, sugary smell when extruding.

Standard PLA has a quick transition from molten to solid, enabling it to provide more detail than other plastics.

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota. We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Standard PLA plastic filament arrives on a durable plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We use what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415257882736, 'title': 'Standard PLA - Snow White', 'handle': 'ingeo-pla-standard-white', 'description': '

Architectural and engineering models look fantastic in Snow White, one of our most popular colors of Standard PLA 3D printer filament. If you can\'t decide which color of Standard PLA to go with, you can never go wrong with Snow White; it is an excellent pick.

Our Standard PLA, or Polylactic Acid, is among the most popular 3D printing materials in the world because it is easy to print and strong. Standard PLA is a hard plastic that produces a barely noticeable, but quite pleasant, sugary smell when extruding.

Standard PLA has a quick transition from molten to solid, enabling it to provide more detail than other plastics.

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota. We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Standard PLA plastic filament arrives on a durable plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We use what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415259848816, 'title': 'Glass Filled PLA Industrial Gray', 'handle': 'glass-filled-pla', 'description': '

Glass Filled PLA 3D printer filament is a first-of-its-kind engineering-grade filament that can be used on any machine capable of printing standard PLA.

Glass Filled PLA filament offers similar benefits of standard PLA such as a very low warp, low odor, and no special extruder or heated bed needed. But the power of its composite make-up allows it to be stronger, tougher and more flexible.

In a comparison to parts 3D printed in standard PLA, Glass Filled PLA is:

  • 1.4 times stronger than PLA at 57 MPa of max tensile strength.
  • 1.3 times tougher than PLA with 34 J/m of Impact Toughness.
  • 1.9 times more flexible than PLA with a tensile elongation of 3.4% before failure.

Glass Filled PLA is an effort to advance engineered and practical-use 3D printed parts and components, but also to simply offer to users of PLA a product far improved.

Print Settings
Glass Filled PLA prints well at 190-210 C. These are general starting points for Glass Filled PLA, actual temperatures will vary from one printer to another. A heated bed is not necessary, though if you have one, set it to 40 C.

Filament Information Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Download Glass-Filled Brochure in PDF Format

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: 500g (1.1lbs) of Glass Filled PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.\xa0

{'id': 1415260602480, 'title': 'Wound Up - Coffee Filament', 'handle': 'wound-coffee-filled-filament', 'description': '

Where's the JAVA?
Due to raw material and production issues, we will probably not have more Wound Up filament available for a few more weeks. Please accept our apologies as we work out the issues.

You can still order any remaining inventory available.

3D printing with coffee!

Wound Up™ is a coffee filled 3D printing filament made using waste byproducts from coffee. Wound Up™ uses those coffee left-overs to create a special 3D printing material with visibly unique print finishes. The filament produces products with a rich brown color and a noticeable natural grain. Now a cup printed with Wound Up™ is a true “coffee cup.”

CAUTION: Wound Up™ coffee filament uses PLA as its base polymer. Because of this, you should NOT use it for 3D printing anything that will come in contact with high heat or hot liquids. In other words, it IS NOT safe to print a functional coffee cup with this material. We do recommend that you print coffee accessories, such as this coffee bag lid.

Not Just Coffee Filament
This is the first in a line of intriguing materials from 3D-Fuel called the c2composites. More distinctive bio-based products will be released in the near future. Wound Up™ filament can be printed on any machine capable of printing with PLA using standard PLA settings.

Filament Information Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Download the Wound Up Brochure

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: 500g (1.1lbs) of Landfillament plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.\xa0

{'id': 1415262109808, 'title': 'Buzzed - Beer Filament', 'handle': 'buzzed-beer-filament', 'description': '

Where's the Beer?
Due to raw material and production issues, we will probably not have more Buzzed filament available for a few more weeks. Please accept our apologies as we work out the issues.

You can still order any remaining inventory available.

3D print with beer filament!
Buzzed is a beer based 3D printing filament made using waste byproducts from the beer making process. Buzzed uses those beer left-overs to create a special 3D printing material. 3D printing with Buzzed beer filament results in visibly unique print finishes. The filament produces products with a rich golden color and a noticeable natural grain. Now a stein printed with Buzzed is a true “beer stein.”

Note: Because this material uses bio-waste, color may vary from batch to batch.

This is the second in a line of intriguing materials from 3D-Fuel called the c2composites. More distinctive bio-based products will be released soon. Buzzed beer filament can be printed on any machine capable of printing with PLA using standard PLA settings. The beer mug design is a remix of Masskrug - bavarian beerstein by sgb33

Print Settings:
Buzzed prints well at 180-210 C. In general, a good starting point is 10 degrees cooler than you typically print PLA. A heated bed is not necessary, though if you have one, set it to 45 C.

Filament Information Quality:
All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel USA filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance:
Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information:
500g (1.1lbs) of Buzzed Beer Filament plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

Download a Buzzed™ brochure in PDF format

{'id': 1415263322224, 'title': 'Entwined v2 - Hemp Filament', 'handle': 'entwined-hemp-filament', 'description': '

Entwined™ is hemp 3D printer filament, the first and only commercially-available 3D printing filament produced from USA-grown and processed industrial hemp. Industrial hemp crops require no herbicides, no pesticides and grow more densely compared to corn. Entwined hemp filament uses no dyes, allowing it to maintain a true natural brown. There's a large amount of visible bio-fill, something you don't get with standard PLA. This is the third in a line of intriguing materials as part of a continuing partnership between 3D-Fuel and bio-composite company, c2renew. More distinctive bio-based products will be released soon.

Entwined Hemp-Filled PLA is made with a percentage of Hemp byproducts, including hurd and fiber, and Workday PLA.\xa0

We've reduced the particle size of the hemp material and increased the percentage. This will enable printing in a much wider variety of 3D printers. If you had a tricky time printing with Entwined in the past, the new formulation is much better.

Entwined hemp filament can be printed on any machine capable of printing with PLA using standard PLA settings.

Entwined SDS
Entwined TDS

Print Settings
Entwined prints well at 180-210 C. In general, a good starting point is 10 degrees cooler than you typically print PLA. A heated bed is not necessary, though if you have one, set it to 45-60 C.

Filament Information Quality:
All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel USA filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance:
Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information:
500g (1.1 lbs) or 1 kg (2.2 lbs) of Entwined Hemp Filament plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture. Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including MakerBot, Raise3D,\xa0LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible. Download an Entwined™ brochure in PDF format

{'id': 1415264370800, 'title': 'Workday PLA - Midnight Black', 'handle': 'workday-pla-midnight-black', 'description': '

Midnight Black is our most popular color! It is great for everything from prototypes to complete models. It prints well, it looks good and it is your basic Go-To color for most engineers and makers!

Workday PLA is made from NatureWorks™ 3D850 and is the first plastic ever designed from the beginning to be used in 3D Printing!

Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, Midnight Black Workday PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. You can anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance than ABS.

Our Workday PLA is the first 3D Filament ever made from plastic that was engineered and designed with 3D Printing in mind. All others before have been made from plastic designed for injection molding and do not have the advanced characteristics for 3D Printing. It actually outperforms standard PLA and even ABS!

[Formerly known as Fossil Fuel Black]

Additional Product Info

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Midnight Black\xa0Workday PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415264796784, 'title': 'Workday PLA - Industrial Gray', 'handle': 'workday-pla-industrial-gray', 'description': '

Workday PLA is made from NatureWorks™ 3D850 and is the first plastic ever designed from the beginning to be used in 3D Printing!

Some customers call this "model gray" because it's just the right color for matching the plastic that model ships and planes are made from.\xa0

Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, Industrial Gray Workday PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. You can anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance than ABS.

Our Workday PLA is the first 3D Filament ever made from plastic that was engineered and designed with 3D Printing in mind. All others before have been made from plastic designed for injection molding and do not have the advanced characteristics for 3D Printing. It actually outperforms standard PLA and even ABS!

[Formerly known as Battleship Gray]

Additional Product Info

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Industrial Gray\xa0Workday PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415265910896, 'title': 'Workday PLA - Electric Blue', 'handle': 'advanced-pla-electric-blue', 'description': '

Workday PLA is made from NatureWorks™ 3D850 and is the first plastic ever designed from the beginning to be used in 3D Printing!

Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, Electric Blue Workday PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. You can anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance than ABS.

Our Workday PLA is the first 3D Filament ever made from plastic that was engineered and designed with 3D Printing in mind. All others before have been made from plastic designed for injection molding and do not have the advanced characteristics for 3D Printing. It actually outperforms standard PLA and even ABS!

Additional Product Info

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Electric Blue\xa0Workday PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415267254384, 'title': 'Workday PLA - Tangerine Orange', 'handle': 'advanced-pla-tangerine-orange', 'description': '

Tangerine Orange is a great color for any bright orange project. It stands out, looks beautiful and prints great!

Workday PLA is made from NatureWorks™ 3D850 and is the first plastic ever designed from the beginning to be used in 3D Printing!

Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, Tangerine Orange Workday PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. You can anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance than ABS.

Our Workday PLA is the first 3D Filament ever made from plastic that was engineered and designed with 3D Printing in mind. All others before have been made from plastic designed for injection molding and do not have the advanced characteristics for 3D Printing. It actually outperforms standard PLA and even ABS!

[Formerly known as Napalm Orange]

Additional Product Info

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Tangerine Orange\xa0Workday PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415268368496, 'title': 'Workday PLA - Snow White', 'handle': 'workday-pla-snow-white', 'description': '

Snow White is our 2nd most popular color! It is great for everything from prototypes to complete models. It prints well, it looks good and it is a\xa0basic Go-To color for most engineers and makers!

Workday PLA is made from NatureWorks™ 3D850 and is the first plastic ever designed from the beginning to be used in 3D Printing!

Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, Snow White Workday PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. You can anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance than ABS.

Our Workday PLA is the first 3D Filament ever made from plastic that was engineered and designed with 3D Printing in mind. All others before have been made from plastic designed for injection molding and do not have the advanced characteristics for 3D Printing. It actually outperforms standard PLA and even ABS!

[Formerly known as High Octane White]

Additional Product Info

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Snow White\xa0Workday PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415269023856, 'title': 'Workday PLA - Island Fuchsia', 'handle': 'advanced-pla-island-fuchsia', 'description': '

Now This Is your Pink!\xa0Island Fuchsia is a really hot and tropical color for your special projects!

Workday PLA is made from NatureWorks™ 3D850 and is the first plastic ever designed from the beginning to be used in 3D Printing!

Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, Island Fuchsia Workday PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. You can anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance than ABS.

Our Workday PLA is the first 3D Filament ever made from plastic that was engineered and designed with 3D Printing in mind. All others before have been made from plastic designed for injection molding and do not have the advanced characteristics for 3D Printing. It actually outperforms standard PLA and even ABS!

[Otherwise known as Hot Pink]

Additional Product Info

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Island Fuchsia\xa0Workday PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415272431728, 'title': 'Landfillament - Trash', 'handle': 'landfillament-garbage-filament', 'description': '

Where's the Trash?

Due to raw material and production issues, we will probably not have more Landfillament available for a few more weeks.
Please accept our apologies as we work out the issues.

You can still order any remaining inventory available.\xa0

3D print with hot garbage!

Landfillament is a 3D printing filament made using upcycled garbage. On location, the upcycled garbage, from which metals have been removed, is run through a process called pyrolysis - a thermochemical decomposition of organic material at high temperatures in the absence of oxygen. During pyrolysis, a char byproduct is created.

The black char byproduct can be used for many things, including composite plastic 3D printing filament. The gas byproducts produced in this process are also captured for new uses. Because of this process, each spool of Landfillament sequesters .909lbs of CO2e (carbon dioxide equivalent) which is the equivalent amount of greenhouse gas emitted by a car driven 1.1 miles.

This is the fourth in a line of intriguing materials from 3D-Fuel called the c2composites. More distinctive bio-based products will be released soon.

Landfillament - Upcycled Garbage Filament can be printed on any machine capable of printing with PLA using standard PLA settings.

Print Settings
Landfillament prints well at 180-210 C. In general, a good starting point is 10 degrees cooler than you typically print PLA. A heated bed is not necessary, though if you have one, set it to 45 C.

Filament Information Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Download the Landfillament Brochure

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: 500g (1.1lbs) of Landfillament plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.\xa0

{'id': 1415272890480, 'title': 'Pro PLA - Natural', 'handle': 'pro-pla-natural', 'description': '

Our Pro PLA is the best PLA product available for printing your projects. Made from NatureWorks™ 3D870 Ingeo PLA, it offers a third-generation level of design for 3D-Printing due to the engineering put into the plastic. And... it's made from corn!

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

Pro PLA boasts 4.3 times the impact strength of PLA. Even before post-processing, Pro PLA exhibits significantly higher impact strength than ABS.

Download SDS

Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 210-240C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Fire Engine Red Pro PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

{'id': 1415273382000, 'title': 'rPETG - 100% Recycled PETG - Natural', 'handle': 'rpetg', 'description': '

Manufacture from 100% recycled PETG, rPETG is a fantastic, economical 3D printing material. PETG has fantastic optical properties, resulting in nearly transparent prints with amazing light transmission. Different layer heights and print settings will affect how your 3D printed parts pass light.

PETG is a newer printing filament with the advantage of printing easily like PLA, but offering higher temp and impact resistance like ABS. Nearly ZERO warpage prints, extremely strong layer bonds, little to no odor at all. rPETG is a recycled PETG and as a result will have slightly different physical properties than virgin PETG filaments.

Recommended Print Settings (settings will vary from printer to printer)

Print nozzle temp:\xa0235 - 260C

Heated Bed temp:\xa060 - 90C

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Natural rPETG plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415273807984, 'title': 'Pro PLA - Industrial Gray', 'handle': 'pro-pla-industrial-gray', 'description': '

Our Pro PLA is the best PLA product available for printing your projects. Made from NatureWorks™ 3D870 Ingeo PLA, it offers a third-generation level of design for 3D-Printing due to the engineering put into the plastic. And... it's made from corn!

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

Pro PLA boasts 4.3 times the impact strength of PLA. Even before post-processing, Pro PLA exhibits significantly higher impact strength than ABS.

Download SDS

Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 210-240C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

{'id': 1415275806832, 'title': 'HydroSupport - Water Soluble Support Material', 'handle': 'hydrosupport-water-soluble-support-material', 'description': '

HydroSupport dissolves completely in water and is much easier to print with than PVA filament. Because it dissolves in water, HydroSupport only needs to be soaked a few hours to easily work supports off by hand, or 2 - 12 hours to dissolve completely. The process can be sped up further by using warm water and agitation. For example, by using a heated ultrasonic tank. HydroSupport is non-toxic, meaning it can be rinsed down the drain without harming the environment or wildlife. HydroSupport has a high tensile strength and feels like PLA when printing is complete. Use it as a support material to print large overhangs, intricate inner geometry, and deep cavities.

NOTE: Because HydroSupport breaks down in water, it is sensitive to high levels of humidity in the air. For best results store unused HydroSupport filament in a sealed container with desiccant.

Download the HydroSupport v1 MSDS

Print Settings

Extruder: 215 - 230 C
Build plate: 45 - 60 C
Speeds: Start with your favorite PLA settings
Retraction Distance: 1 - 10 mm
Retraction Speed: 20 mm/s

Every 3D printer is a little different, so please experiment a bit to dial in your ideal settings before starting a large project. We find that reducing the gap between supports and model to 0.00 mm helps with adhesion and surface finish. HydroSupport will commonly ooze more than PLA. If you have the option of using an ooze shield and purge tower, please do.

Quality:
All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance:
Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.\xa0Available in 1.75mm or 2.85mm diameters.

Packing Information:
500g (1.1lbs) of HydroSupport - Water Soluble Support filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing:
The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including MakerBot, Raise3D, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

Our Pro PLA is the best PLA product available for printing your projects. Made from NatureWorks™ 3D870 Ingeo PLA, it offers a third-generation level of design for 3D-Printing due to the engineering put into the plastic. And... it's made from corn!

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

Pro PLA boasts 4.3 times the impact strength of PLA. Even before post-processing, Pro PLA exhibits significantly higher impact strength than ABS.

{'id': 1415276789872, 'title': 'Pro PLA - Ocean Blue', 'handle': 'pro-pla-ocean-blue', 'description': '

Our Pro PLA is the best PLA product available for printing your projects. Made from NatureWorks™ 3D870 Ingeo PLA, it offers a third-generation level of design for 3D-Printing due to the engineering put into the plastic. And... it's made from corn!

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

Pro PLA boasts 4.3 times the impact strength of PLA. Even before post-processing, Pro PLA exhibits significantly higher impact strength than ABS.

Download SDS

Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 210-240C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Fire Engine Red Pro PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

Natural Standard PLA is great for a basic material for 3D printing prototypes. This PLA does have a slight, yellowish hue in its natural form.
(Note: The photo shows our old beige spool. The actual spool you will receive will be black.)

Natural Standard PLA\xa0printed parts will always look great.\xa0The neutral coloring is translucent and allows you to see the object, not the color of the object.

Our Standard PLA, or Polylactic Acid, is among the most popular 3D printing materials in the world because it is easy to print and strong. Standard PLA is a hard plastic that produces a barely noticeable, but quite pleasant, sugary smell when extruding.

Standard PLA has a quick transition from molten to solid, enabling it to provide more detail than other plastics.

{'id': 1415279902832, 'title': 'Pro PLA - Tangerine Orange', 'handle': 'pro-pla-tangerine-orange', 'description': '

Our Pro PLA is the best PLA product available for printing your projects. Made from NatureWorks™ 3D870 Ingeo PLA, it offers a third-generation level of design for 3D-Printing due to the engineering put into the plastic. And... it's made from corn!

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

Pro PLA boasts 4.3 times the impact strength of PLA. Even before post-processing, Pro PLA exhibits significantly higher impact strength than ABS.

Download SDS

Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 210-240C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of\xa0Tangerine Orange Pro PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1415281770608, 'title': 'Standard PLA - Ocean Blue', 'handle': 'standard-pla-ocean-blue', 'description': 'Ocean Blue Standard PLA is great for a basic material for 3D printing prototypes.

Standard PLA\xa0printed parts always look great.\xa0And if blue is your color, you\'ll love our Ocean Blue Filament!

Our Standard PLA, or Polylactic Acid, is among the most popular 3D printing materials in the world because it is easy to print and strong. Standard PLA is a hard plastic that produces a barely noticeable, but quite pleasant, sugary smell when extruding.

Standard PLA has a quick transition from molten to solid, enabling it to provide more detail than other plastics.

Download a Brochure
Download SDS
Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 185-215C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota. We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Standard PLA plastic filament arrives on a durable plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We use what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 1570494087280, 'title': 'Workday ABS - Midnight Black', 'handle': '3d-fuel-abs-3d-filament-black', 'description': '

Workday ABS (Acrylonitrile Butadiene Styrene) is a go-to material for projects that require durability and the ability to withstand high temperatures. Our unique formulation is low-warp and low odor.

ABS is used for high strength applications and is a petroleum-based material product, so it holds up well in a variety\xa0of environment. ABS requires a heated bed and works best with an enclosed print area. ABS can produce some off-gassing so it is recommended that you use it only in a well-ventilated area.\xa0

  • Low warp
  • Low odor
  • Heat resistant
  • Durable
  • Mildly flexible
  • can be sanded or smoothed with additional processing\xa0

Check your printer for compatibility before ordering.

  • Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm
  • Extruder: 240-260º C
  • Bed: 100-110º C
  • Bed material:\xa0PEI,\xa0Buildtak, or bare glass +\xa0hair spray
  • Fan Speed: 10% (may vary from printer to printer)
  • Works with most printers that have the temperature capacity
  • 1Kg Spool

Our tester had this to say about Workday ABS:

    "The filament is incredibly easy to print, no modification or settings needed to be changed from PLA [except for print temps]. There was no brim or warping observed in the models, which is truly bewitching comparison to\xa0experience\xa0with previous ABS filaments in\xa0[my]\xa0printer."\xa0

{'id': 1933401030721, 'title': 'HydroPro - Professional Water Soluble Filament', 'handle': 'hydropro-professional-water-soluble-filament', 'description': '

HydroPro™ dissolves quickly and completely in water and is easier to print with than other water-soluble materials such as PVA and PVOH.

HydroPro™ is non-toxic and fully biodegradable, meaning it can be rinsed down the drain without harming the environment or wildlife.

Superpower

HydroPro™ only needs to be soaked for 1-2 hours to easily work supports off by hand, or 2-6 hours to dissolve completely.

Best Suited For

Use it as a support material to print large overhangs, intricate inner geometry, and deep cavities.

Download the HydroPro SDS

Print Settings

Extruder:\xa0210 - 230 C\xa0
Build plate:\xa045 - 60 C\xa0
Speeds:\xa0Start with your favorite PLA settings\xa0
Retraction Distance:\xa01 - 10 mm\xa0
Retraction Speed:\xa020 mm/s

Bed Material

PEI, Buildtak recommended with a heated build plate (45-60° C)

Note

Because HydroPro™ breaks down in the water, it is sensitive to high levels of humidity in the air. For best results, store unused HydroPro™ filament in a sealed container with desiccant.

{'id': 1999041462337, 'title': 'Workday PETG - Natural', 'handle': 'workday-petg-natural', 'description': '

Manufactured from 100% virgin PETG resin, Workday PETG is a fantastic, economical 3D printing material. Natural Workday PETG filament has fantastic optical properties, resulting in nearly transparent prints with amazing light transmission. Different layer heights and print settings will affect how your 3D printed parts pass light.

PETG is a newer printing filament with the advantage of printing easily like PLA, but offering higher temp and impact resistance like ABS. Nearly ZERO warpage prints, extremely strong layer bonds, little to no odor at all.\xa0

Recommended Print Settings (settings will vary from printer to printer)

Print nozzle temp:\xa0235 - 260C

Heated Bed temp:\xa060 - 90C

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of Natural Workday PETG plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

Manufactured from 100% virgin PETG resin, Workday PETG is a fantastic, economical 3D printing material.\xa0Midnight Black Workday PETG filament has the advantage of printing easily like PLA, but offering higher temp and impact resistance like ABS. Recommended Print Settings (settings will vary from printer to printer)

Print nozzle temp:\xa0235 - 260C

Heated Bed temp:\xa060 - 90C

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of\xa0Midnight Black Workday PETG plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

{'id': 2074567082049, 'title': 'Pro PLA - Daffodil Yellow', 'handle': 'pro-pla-daffodil-yellow', 'description': '

Our Pro PLA is the best PLA product available for printing your projects. Made from NatureWorks™ 3D870 Ingeo PLA, it offers a third-generation level of design for 3D-Printing due to the engineering put into the plastic. And... it's made from corn!

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

Pro PLA boasts 4.3 times the impact strength of PLA. Even before post-processing, Pro PLA exhibits significantly higher impact strength than ABS.

Download SDS

Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 210-240C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of\xa0Daffodil Yellow Pro PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 2118169624641, 'title': 'SnapSupport™ Breakaway Support Material - 3D450 from NatureWorks™', 'handle': 'snapsupport-breakaway-material-made-with-3d450-from-natureworks', 'description': '

SnapSupport is a new breakaway material made with Ingeo 3D450 resin from NatureWorks.\xa0The clean, fast mechanical break-away of\xa0SnapSupport support structures results in parts with high finish quality, reducing post-processing time and improving overall productivity.

\n

Applications for SnapSupport support material include complex industrial parts such as jigs and fixtures, patterns for investment metal casting, and architectural and retail models. SnapSupport, made with Ingeo 3D450 is designed to work with the Ingeo 3D series of grades, including 3D850 (3D-Fuel Workday PLA) and 3D870 (3D-Fuel Pro PLA) that were developed for the professional printing market. At printing speeds up to 100 mm/s, SnapSupport prints and cools without warping even across large sections of support structures.

\n

The SnapSupport’s break-away formulation can reduce or eliminate speed and build-ability issues sometimes encountered with soluble support materials such as polyvinyl alcohol (PVA) or high-impact polystyrene (HIPS). Compared to these soluble supports, SnapSupport has a longer and more stable shelf life, dramatically reduced moisture sensitivity during printing, and reduces the need for post-processing with its clean break-away from a build. The new grade is compatible with large format printers, and since SnapSupport break-away supports do not rely on solvent baths for removal, SnapSupport avoids the size constraints encountered with needing to submerse a build.

{'id': 2124080054337, 'title': 'Earthen - Cotton Filled PLA', 'handle': 'cotton-filled-pla-by-c2renew', 'description': '

Where's the Cotton?
Due to raw material and production issues, we will probably not have more Earthen filament available for a few more weeks. Please accept our apologies as we work out the issues.

You can still order any remaining inventory available.

3D print with cotton filament!

Earthen is a cotton-based 3D printing filament made using waste byproducts from the cotton industry. Earthen uses cotton waste to create a special 3D printing material. 3D printing with Earthen cotton filament results in visibly unique print finishes. The filament produces products with a unique earth-tone color palette.

Note: Because this material uses biomass, color may vary from batch to batch.

This is the sixth in a line of intriguing materials from 3D-Fuel called the c2composites. More distinctive bio-based products will be released soon. Earthen cotton filament can be printed on any machine capable of printing with PLA using standard PLA settings.

Print Settings:

Earthen prints well at 180-210 C. In general, a good starting point is 10 degrees cooler than you typically print PLA. A heated bed is not necessary, though if you have one, set it to 45 C.

Filament Information Quality:

All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool. Learn more about 3D-Fuel USA filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance:

Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information:

Earthen Cotton Filament plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing:

The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 3669505540161, 'title': 'Dow OBC (Olefin Block Copolymer) Filament', 'handle': 'evolv3d-3d-fuel-obc-olefin-block-copolymer-3d-filament', 'description': '

Low Density, High Strength, Excellent Chemical Resistance, Flexible

Polyethylene (PE)-based\xa0Olefin Block Copolymer (OBC) is made from a unique polyethylene-based material.

3D-Fuel, in partnership with Dow Chemical Company, have produced the IMAGIN3D™ OBC filament - a breakthrough material that brings polyolefin properties to 3D printing without the issues commonly associated with printing polypropylene.

OBC is a high-performance build material that enables the production of lightweight and durable 3D printed parts. It is best suited for 3D printers who need a high quality, lightweight chemical resistant filament. \xa0This new material offers some great characteristics including:

  • Excellent Printability
  • Low Density (0.905 g/cm^3)
  • Higher Durability
  • Excellent z-axis property retention
  • Chemical Resistance
  • Consistent Printing
  • and\xa0Low Odor

These material benefits enable new, high-end applications. OBC’s low flexural modulus and extreme fatigue resistance make living hinges easier and longer-lasting than ever. The low-density, durability, and chemical resistance are excellent for UAV, automotive, marine, and R/C applications.

For best results, use a PP- or PE-based build surface. Clear packing tape is an excellent, low-cost build surface option.

NOTE: Because DOW OBC is such a low-density material, the spool weights are lower than you might expect, but a full spool of OBC (768g) will print the same amount of parts as a 1kg spool of PLA. Pretty crazy, right? It's an excellent material for doing weight-reduction on your 3D printing projects.

Printing parameters:

Print Speed: \xa0 10-40 mm/s

{'id': 3934626644033, 'title': 'Pro PLA - Electric Blue', 'handle': 'pro-pla-electric-blue', 'description': '

Our Pro PLA is the best PLA product available for printing your projects. Made from NatureWorks™ 3D870 Ingeo PLA, it offers a third-generation level of design for 3D-Printing due to the engineering put into the plastic. And... it's made from corn!

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

Pro PLA boasts 4.3 times the impact strength of PLA. Even before post-processing, Pro PLA exhibits significantly higher impact strength than ABS.

Download SDS

Download TDS

Recommended Printing Temperature: 210-240C*

Recommended Bed Temperature: 0-60C*

Recommended Print Speed: 40 – 100 mm/s

Quality: All 3D-Fuel 3D printer filament is manufactured in our own production facility located in Fargo, North Dakota or in Moville, Ireland (depending on customer location). We have complete control over the manufacturing process and are able to ensure consistent quality for every spool.

Learn more about 3D-Fuel filament quality.

Diameter Tolerance: Variable diameter can cause big problems in your 3D printer. We use a multi-axis laser measurement system to control our filament diameter and ovality in real time during production. Every spool has the diameter and ovality measurements listed right on the box.

Packing Information: A full 1kg (2.2lbs) of\xa0Electric Blue Pro PLA plastic filament arrives on an easy-to-use plastic reel and is vacuum sealed with a desiccant packet to keep out any moisture.

Test Printing: The 3D-Fuel test lab features multiple brands of 3D printers including Raise3D, MakerBot, LulzBot, FlashForge, and more. We 3D print what we manufacture to ensure that our filament provides the absolute best quality possible.

{'id': 4162584281153, 'title': 'Pro PLA - Iron Red', 'handle': 'pro-pla-iron-red', 'description': '

Our Pro PLA is the best PLA product available for printing your projects. Made from NatureWorks™ 3D870 Ingeo PLA, it offers a third-generation level of design for 3D-Printing due to the engineering put into the plastic. And... it's made from corn!

Pro PLA has higher impact strength than ABS and Standard PLA with a heat resistance rivaling that of ABS! Available in 1.75mm and 2.85mm diameter, new Pro PLA will help your 3D printed projects look amazing and perform amazingly. Anneal your design after 3D printing for even better heat resistance.

Our Pro PLA is engineered and designed specifically with 3D Printing in mind. Pro PLA was designed with the high impact strength needed in industrial applications to meet the growing demand by companies for a material with the properties of ABS, but the printability of PLA.

Pro PLA boasts 4.3 times the impact strength of PLA. Even before post-processing, Pro PLA exhibits significantly higher impact strength than ABS.

{'id': 4406523822145, 'title': 'Out of Spec and Transition PLA Spools - READ FULL DESCRIPTION', 'handle': 'out-of-spec-and-transition-pla-spools-read-full-description', 'description': '

Up to 1kg of filament for only $7?

We make a LOT of filament. And we have VERY HIGH standards. The result of these two facts is that we end up with spools that don't make the cut. For one reason or another, they aren't good enough to have us put in our 3D-Fuel brand boxes. They are not necessarily too bad to use, but they just don't meet our standards.\xa0

Reasons we\xa0cull filament could include one (or more) of the following:

  • Not enough to fill a spool (< 1kg of material)
  • The diameter fell out of our desired range (Usually 0.03mm max)
  • The ovality was not close enough for us to accept it
  • There was a color transition while the spool was being made
  • There may be a bubble somewhere in the spool

In general, we only keep spools that have 80% or more of the needed filament on them. If it's less than 1/2 a spool, we pull the filament off, recycle it, and then re-use the spool. If it's higher, we put a label on it to tell why we're culling it and then vacuum seal it with desiccant like we do our other products.

Conditions to ordering:

  1. All spools are\xa0sold\xa0"AS-IS" - No Guarantee Whatsoever
  2. Spools are non-returnable and non-refundable
  3. Spools may NOT be sold as 3D-Fuel branded product
  4. You CAN combine these with other items to get Free Shipping!
  5. Wholesale buyers can get free shipping on 100+ spools
  6. You CANNOT Choose Color or Type. We just pull the next roll.\xa0

1kg Sized Spools will have 600-1000g on them.

4Kg Sized spools will have more than 3kg on them.\xa0

Price is subject to change without notice.
